        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:22PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 30 miles east of Port Aransas to near Mustang
Island State Park to near Kings Crossing Subdivision to near Riviera
Beach. Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Corpus Christi, Port Aransas, Riviera Beach, Flour Bluff, Corpus
Christi Country Club, Packery Channel, South Texas Botanical Gardens,
Kings Crossing Subdivision, Padre Balli Park, Bay Area Medical
Center, Mustang Island State Park, Spohn Hospital South, Riviera,
Texas A&amp;M University Corpus Christi, Waldron Field, La Palmera Mall,
Loyola Beach, Chapman Ranch, and Corpus Christi Naval Air Station.

This includes US Highway 77 between mile markers 706 and 708.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
